(b) Key decision points / tradeoffs:
- Diagnosis vs. speed: I chose a short, structured discovery (stakeholder interviews + data pull) over jumping straight to fixes, to avoid optimizing the wrong bottleneck.

- Established baseline metrics and a weekly dashboard; implemented a new intake/triage rubric and clearer handoff criteria.

- Result: materially reduced cycle time and rework (double-digit improvements) and improved stakeholder satisfaction/clarity of ownership; the process remained in place after handoff due to clear owners + instrumentation.

(d) What I would do differently:
- Involve downstream teams earlier in the pilot design to reduce later change-management effort.
- Add a pre-mortem earlier to surface edge cases sooner.
